
OBJECTS

class is just a blueprint

class Cab
is not a actual cab
It's only instructions for how a cab should look.

An object is the actual thing created from that blueprint

Creating objects:

1. MOST COMMON WAY - CONSTRUCTOR

data class ClassName(val variable: Datatype)  -- constructor
ClassName("value")                       -- object created

2. FACTORY METHOD

a factory method like factory.createCab(...) is called and it will return the object for me
still inside the function i will call the constructor and return the object

3. SINGLETON

object DataBase{
    val connection: Connection
    fun connect() {}
}

DataBase.connection
DataBase.connect()

There is already one object.
You don't create it.
It already exists.

No constructor call.

Because object already exists.



